'''Carlos P<U+00E9>rez Su<U+00E1>rez''' (born July 14, 1994 in [[Guadalajara, Jalisco]], [[Mexico]]) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]] in the [[Light Welterweight]] division.<ref>http://boxrec.com/list_bouts.php?human_id=514055&cat=boxer</ref> Carlos is promoted by current [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] Champion, [[Mexican people|Mexican]] [[Sa<U+00FA>l <U+00C1>lvarez]]' company Canelo Promotions.<ref>http://www.boxeomundial.net/boxeo.php?category=noticias&id=22659</ref>

==Amateur career==
During his amateur career he had seventeen fights, going 16-1.<ref>http://canelopromotions.com.mx/boxeadores/grandes_prospectos.php</ref>

==Professional career==
In December 2010, P<U+00E9>rez beat the veteran Ivan Rodriguez at the Arena Jalisco in [[Guadalajara, Jalisco]], [[Mexico]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=611100</ref>

In his next fight Carlos lost against the veteran Cesar Figueroa, on the undercard [[Sa<U+00FA>l <U+00C1>lvarez vs. Ryan Rhodes]].<ref>http://boxrec.com/show_display.php?show_id=618166</ref>

